        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 2 at 6:12PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 612 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Richwood, or 10 miles south of Monroe, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Richwood, Pine Grove, Fondale and Bosco.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
